1. e3 Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 b6 4. Nc3 Bb7 5. d4 Bb4 {Via a very unusual move
order we are back in the Nimzo-Indian.} 6. Bd3 Ne4 7. O-O $1 {White can
sacrifice the pawn since he gets a serious initiative if Black takes it.} Bxc3
8. bxc3 O-O (8... Nxc3 9. Qc2 Bxf3 10. gxf3 Qg5+ 11. Kh1 Qh5 12. Rg1 $1 Qxf3+
13. Rg2 f5 14. Ba3 $1 $36 {1-0 (25) Keres,P-Spassky,B Riga 1965}) 9. Ne1 $3 {
Now taking on c3 loses a piece, so White prepares f3 without losing time.} c5 (
9... f5 {is best in my opinion, though after} 10. f3 Nf6 11. Qe2 d6 12. e4 {
White has some advantage.}) (9... Nxc3 $4 10. Qc2 $18) 10. f3 Nf6 11. e4 {
The knight on e1 may look misplaced but in fact the opposite is true: the
knight can reach its optimal square on e3 via c2!} Ne8 (11... d6 12. Bg5 h6 13.
Bh4 e5 14. Nc2 Nbd7 15. d5 Qc7 16. Ne3 $16) 12. d5 d6 13. Nc2 Nd7 14. Ne3 Nef6
({After} 14... e5 {White can execute the familiar plan with Ra2:} 15. a4 a5 16.
g3 Ba6 17. Ra2 $1) (14... Ne5 {is not effective. For example} 15. Be2 Ba6 16.
f4 Nd7 17. Bd3 e5 18. f5 Nc7 19. a4 f6 20. g4 h6 21. h4 Qe7 22. Ra2 $1 $18) 15.
a4 a5 16. Ra2 Qc7 ({If} 16... e5 {then} 17. g3 $1 {is best, intending f4.} (17.
f4 {Even if White is still better after this, playing f4 should be avoided if
Black's knight can occupy the e5-square.}) (17. g4 $5 {is also good.})) 17. f4
exd5 (17... e5 {Here, I would have played} 18. f5 {when White's position is
winning for sure, though it may take some time.} (18. fxe5 {could also be
considered, with the idea to sacrifice the exchange after} Nxe5 (18... dxe5 19.
g4 Ne8 20. Rg2 Nd6 21. h4 $18 {White will prepare a decisive breakthrough -
Black has not counterplay at all.}) 19. Rxf6 $1 gxf6 20. Ng4 $1 {White has a
winning attack after exchanging Black's strongest defensive piece.} (20. Nf5 $5
) (20. Rf2 $5))) 18. exd5 $3 $18 {Keeping Black's queenside pieces boxed in.
Now Carlsen has a free hand on the kingside.} (18. cxd5 c4 $3 {would have
given Black counterplay.}) 18... Rfe8 19. g4 $3 Nf8 (19... Ne4 20. Qf3 Nxc3 21.
Ra3 $18) 20. g5 N6d7 (20... Ne4 21. Qc2 $18) 21. h4 Rad8 22. h5 Bc8 (22... g6
23. Rh2 $18 (23. h6)) 23. Ng4 Re7 24. Rg2 Kh8 25. Qf3 Rde8 26. Qg3 Rd8 (26...
Nb8 27. f5 $18) (26... f5 27. gxf6 Nxf6 28. Nxf6 gxf6 29. Qg8#) 27. Bd2 Rde8
28. f5 Ne5 29. Nxe5 Rxe5 30. Bf4 Nd7 31. f6 g6 32. hxg6 fxg6 33. Bxg6 hxg6 34.
f7 Rf8 35. Bxe5+ Nxe5 36. Qh4+ Kg7 37. Qh6# 1-0

