1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. g3 O-O 5. Bg2 d6 6. Nf3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Nbd7 8.
Qd3 {This move prepares Nd2 - White wants to control the important e4-square.}
e5 9. Nd2 Re8 10. O-O Qe7 {How should White continue?} 11. e4 $1 {White should
not allow Black to play ...e5-e4.} ({Therefore,} 11. Re1 $2 {is a huge
positional mistake.} e4 12. Qc2 Nf8 {Black would be much better after 12...e3,
but I want to demonstrate that Black is even better with slow play:} (12... e3
$17) 13. Nf1 h5 (13... h6) 14. Bg5 N8h7 $15 {Black is following the so-called
light-square strategy.}) 11... b6 12. Re1 Ba6 13. a4 c5 14. d5 $1 {By blocking
the centre, White prevents any counterplay. Afterwards he can reroute his
knight to the e3-square without being disturbed.} (14. Nf1 cxd4 15. cxd4 exd4
16. Qxd4 Nc5 {White may still be slightly better but Black has counterchances
due to his active pieces play.}) 14... Nf8 15. Nf1 Ng6 16. Bh3 $5 {This is not
obligatory, but it makes perfect sense.} (16. Ne3 {was also possible.}) 16...
Bc8 17. Bxc8 Raxc8 18. Bg5 $6 {In my opinion, his is a mistake. White should
have played 18.Ne3 instead.} ({After} 18. Ne3 Qd7 19. f3 h6 20. Re2 $16 {
White is in full control. The only good thing about Black's position is that
it's solid. However, White should be close to winning strategically.}) 18... h6
19. Bxf6 Qxf6 20. a5 {This is White's idea - he creates a weakness on b6.
However, I don't like this strategy since even in the case White wins the
b6-pawn, he can never create a passed pawn.} Nf8 21. axb6 axb6 22. Ra6 $16 {
White is somewhat better and he won after a tough fight.} Ra8 23. Rea1 Rxa6 24.
Rxa6 Rb8 25. Kg2 Qe7 26. Qb1 Qb7 27. Qb5 Nd7 28. Qa4 Nf6 29. Ra7 Qc8 30. f3 g6
31. Ne3 h5 32. Qc6 Qd8 33. h4 Rc8 34. Qb7 Qf8 35. Nd1 Rb8 36. Qc6 Rc8 37. Qb7
Rb8 38. Qc6 Rc8 39. Qxb6 Rb8 40. Qc7 Rc8 41. Qb7 Rb8 42. Qc7 Rc8 43. Qa5 Qd8
44. Qxd8+ Rxd8 45. Kf2 Kf8 46. Ke2 Rd7 47. Ra6 Ke7 48. Kd2 Rb7 49. Kc2 Ne8 50.
Ne3 Nf6 51. Nf1 Nd7 52. Nd2 Nb8 53. Ra1 Kd8 54. g4 hxg4 55. fxg4 Ke7 56. Nb3
Kf6 57. Ra8 Nd7 58. Na5 Rb8 59. g5+ Kg7 60. Rxb8 Nxb8 61. Nb7 f5 62. exf5 gxf5
63. h5 f4 64. Nxd6 Nd7 65. Kd3 1-0

