natural-looking move is a mistake with our bishop still on b4! It's ok if our
bishop is on d6, e7, or ...f8!} (1... b6 $5 2. f3 Bb7 $5 $13 (2... c5 $5 3. a3
Bxc3 4. bxc3 Ba6)) 2. f3 $1 $16 c5 3. a3 $3 {thats the difference, with the
bishop on b4 !!} Bxc3 (3... cxd4 4. axb4 $3 (4. exd4 $14) 4... dxc3 5. Nxc3 d4
(5... Nc6 6. b5 Ne5 7. Be2 $16) 6. Ne4 $14) 4. bxc3 $16 {Since Black has lost
a tempo playing ...c6-c5, White is a tempo up on an already good version of
the classical position!} *

