1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 5. e3 Bb7 6. Be2 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 O-O 8.
O-O d6 9. a4 a5 10. Re1 Nbd7 11. Nd2 e5 $1 {Black correctly plays actively in
the centre.} ({It is easy to drift into a bad position with passive play. For
example} 11... Re8 $2 12. Bd3 e5 13. e4 Qe7 14. f3 h6 15. Nf1 $16 {White has
all the advantages - the knight is coming to e3 and the queen's rook can be
transferred to the centre via the 2nd rank.}) 12. Bf3 $2 (12. Bd3 e4 $1 13. Bf1
Re8 $17) (12. f3 $142 e4 $1 (12... Ne8 $2 13. e4 $1 f5 $6 14. exf5 Rxf5 15. Bd3
Rf8 16. Ne4 $16) (12... exd4 $2 13. cxd4 $16) 13. f4 $13) 12... e4 $1 13. Be2
Re8 $17 {Now, White is clearly worse - his bishops are boxed in.} 14. f3 exf3
15. Bxf3 Ne4 16. Nxe4 Bxe4 17. Kh1 Qh4 $19 {White tried to create some
activity with f3 but this only led to further weaknesses. Black soon started a
strong attack, based on his strong outpost on e4.} 18. Rf1 Nf6 19. Qe1 Qg5 20.
Qe2 Re7 21. Ra2 Rae8 22. Bxe4 Nxe4 23. Rc2 Re6 24. Rf3 Rh6 25. Qe1 Ree6 26. Kg1
Qh5 27. Rh3 Qg4 28. Rxh6 Rxh6 29. Bb2 Qh5 30. h3 Rg6 31. Kh2 Rg3 32. Re2 Qf5
33. Rf2 Rxh3+ 34. gxh3 Nxf2 35. Qf1 Ng4+ 36. Kg1 Qxf1+ 37. Kxf1 Nxe3+ 38. Ke2
Nxc4 39. Bc1 d5 40. Bf4 c6 41. Bc7 f6 0-1

