Bb7 9. Bg2 Nbd7 10. O-O c5 $5 ({The plan with} 10... a5 11. b3 Be4 {was seen
in the previous game.}) 11. b3 Rc8 12. Bb2 d5 $5 {Black plays very actively in
the centre.} (12... cxd4 $5 {is another possible way to play the position. For
example} 13. Qxd4 (13. Nxd4 $6 {Exchanging the bishops is in Black's favour.}
Bxg2 14. Kxg2 d5 $15) 13... Nc5 14. Qd1 d5 $1 $132 (14... e5 $5 15. b4 Ne6) 15.
cxd5 Bxd5 $15 {Even though the position is opened, White cannot make use of
his pair of bishops. Black's pieces are very active and White has a weakness
on b3.} (15... Qxd5 16. Qxd5 Bxd5 17. b4 Nb3 18. Rad1 $11)) 13. Rfd1 (13. Ne5
$6 Nxe5 14. dxe5 d4 $1 15. Qc2 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Nd7 $15) 13... dxc4 14. Qxc4 ({
Only Black can be better after} 14. bxc4 cxd4 15. Nxd4 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 a6 (16...
Qc7 $5)) 14... Bd5 15. Qd3 Be4 $11 ({Interesting was} 15... c4 $5 16. bxc4 Bxc4
17. Qd2 b5 $5 $132 (17... Bd5 18. a4 $5)) 16. Qd2 cxd4 17. Nxd4 Bxg2 18. Kxg2
Nc5 19. b4 Na4 20. f3 Nd5 21. Kg1 Ndc3 22. Bxc3 Nxc3 $17 23. Re1 (23. Rdc1 $2
Qxd4+ $19) 23... Qd5 24. e4 Qc4 25. Ne2 Rfd8 26. Qxc3 Qxc3 27. Nxc3 Rxc3 28.
Red1 Rxd1+ 29. Rxd1 g5 $3 30. Kg2 Rxa3 31. Rd7 Kg7 32. f4 gxf4 33. gxf4 h5 34.
h4 Re3 35. e5 Ra3 36. f5 exf5 37. e6 Kf6 38. exf7 Kg7 39. b5 f4 40. Rc7 Kf8 41.
Rd7 Kg7 42. Rc7 Ra5 43. Kf3 Rxb5 44. Rxa7 Rf5 45. Rb7 b5 46. Kg2 {WHITE
RESIGNED HERE ...} f3+ 47. Kf2 Kf8 48. Rc7 b4 (48... Rxf7 49. Rc5) 49. Rb7 Rf4
0-1

