1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 Qe7 {Against this line, Black has a very
interesting option:} (4... Bxc3+ $5 5. bxc3 d6 {If White now plays} 6. g3 {
then Black can put his bishop on b7, neutralising the g2-bishop.} b6 7. Bg2 Bb7
{We reach a similar situation in the game.}) 5. g3 b6 6. Bg2 Bb7 7. O-O Bxc3 {
It's good to take the knight, otherwise White may avoid getting doubled pawns.}
8. bxc3 O-O 9. a4 a5 10. Ba3 d6 {Black was about to play ...Nbd7. White
sacrifices a pawn to open the position.} 11. c5 $6 {White gets some
compensation for the pawn, but it's not fully sufficient.} dxc5 12. dxc5 bxc5
13. Rb1 Bc6 14. Qd2 Na6 $17 {Black's extra pawn is securely defended - his
chances are better.} 15. Qg5 Rab8 16. h4 Bxa4 17. h5 h6 18. Qe5 Nd5 19. c4 Ndb4
20. Bb2 f6 21. Qc3 Rfd8 22. Nh4 Bc2 23. Ra1 a4 24. Ng6 Bxg6 25. hxg6 Qd7 26.
Bf3 Rb6 27. Kg2 Rd6 28. Bc1 e5 29. Be3 Qf5 30. Rxa4 e4 31. Bf4 exf3+ 32. exf3
Rd3 33. Qa1 Nb8 34. Ra8 N8c6 35. Rxd8+ Nxd8 36. Qa7 Ne6 37. Re1 Rd8 38. Re4
Nxf4+ 39. Rxf4 Qxg6 40. Qxc7 Rf8 41. Qxc5 Nd3 42. Qd5+ Kh8 43. Rg4 Ne1+ 44. Kf1
Qb1 45. Re4 Nxf3+ 46. Kg2 Ng5 47. Re3 Qb8 48. c5 Rd8 49. Qc4 Qc7 50. c6 Nf7 51.
Rc3 Ne5 52. Qe4 Rd6 53. f4 Rxc6 54. Ra3 Rc2+ 55. Kh3 Qc8+ 56. f5 Rb2 57. Ra8
Rb8 58. Ra7 g6 59. g4 Rb3+ 60. Kh4 g5+ 61. Kh5 Qe8+ 62. Kxh6 Qg6+ 63. fxg6 Rh3#
0-1

