1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 b6 (4... Bxc3+ $5) 5. g3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Bb7
{Black has managed to put his position on b7 - his position is entirely
satisfactory.} 7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O d6 9. Re1 (9. a4 {is always met with} a5) 9...
Nbd7 10. a4 a5 11. Ba3 Re8 {Stepping away from the diagonal of White's bishop.
White's next move appears to be logical, yet it is a mistake.} 12. c5 dxc5 13.
dxc5 Nxc5 {Forcing White to part with his bishop.} 14. Bxc5 bxc5 $15 {White
may be able to reach equality with best play - the position is slightly better
for Black.} 15. Qb3 (15. Ne5 $6 Bxg2 16. Kxg2 Qd5+ 17. Nf3 Rab8 $17) {What
should Black play?} 15... Bd5 $1 {First, Black provokes c4...} 16. c4 Bc6 {
...and then, Black should have taken on f3!} (16... Bxf3 $3 {White's only hope
for active play is connected to moving the knight.} 17. Bxf3 Rb8 18. Qc3 Rb4
19. Bc6 Rf8 20. Red1 Qe7 $17) 17. Qe3 Qe7 18. Ne5 $1 $132 {Now White has some
active play and good compensation.} Bxg2 19. Kxg2 Ra6 20. Rab1 Nd7 21. Nxd7
Qxd7 22. Rb5 Rd6 23. Qxc5 Rc6 24. Rd1 Rxc5 25. Rxd7 Rxc4 26. Rxa5 g5 27. Rxg5+
Kf8 28. a5 Rb8 29. a6 Ra8 30. Ra5 Ra7 31. Rd8+ Kg7 32. Rd3 h6 33. Kf3 Rc6 34.
Rda3 Kg6 35. Kf4 f6 36. e4 Rc2 37. Kf3 Rc6 38. Ke3 Kf7 39. Kd4 Kg7 40. h4 Kg6
41. h5+ Kf7 42. Rc5 Rb6 43. Rac3 Rbxa6 44. Rxc7+ Rxc7 45. Rxc7+ Kg8 46. Re7 Rc6
47. Ke3 Ra6 48. Kf4 Rb6 49. Kg4 Ra6 50. f4 Rb6 51. f5 e5 52. Re6 Rb4 53. Kf3
Kg7 54. Re7+ Kg8 55. Rd7 Rb3+ 56. Kg4 Rb4 57. Rd6 Kg7 58. Rd7+ Kg8 59. Kf3 Rb3+
60. Kg4 Rb4 1/2-1/2

