1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 Ne4 7. Qc2 f5 8.
Nf3 ({A better line for White is} 8. Nh3 d6 9. f3 Nf6 10. e3 $14) 8... b6 9. g3
({In case of} 9. e3 {Black's knight stands perfectly on e4. For example} Bb7
10. Be2 d6 11. O-O Nd7 12. b4 Rf6 {with interesting attacking possibilities.})
9... Bb7 10. Bg2 Nf6 $1 {Black regroups in order to put the bishop on e4. It
seems that Black loses a lot of time, but ...Ne4 was played with tempo, and ...
Be4 will also be played with tempo!} 11. O-O Be4 12. Qc3 Qe8 (12... d6 {
was better in my opinion.}) 13. b4 (13. Bg5 {This is what White should have
played. Black would have liked to play ...Nbd7 to take back on f6 with his
knight.}) 13... d6 14. Re1 Nbd7 15. Bb2 h6 {This seems unnecessary. Black
could have played ...Qh5.} 16. Nd2 (16. d5 {is met with} e5) 16... Bxg2 17.
Kxg2 Ne4 18. Qd3 (18. Nxe4 fxe4 19. Qc2 (19. d5 e5) 19... Nf6 20. d5 e5 $15)
18... Nxd2 19. Qxd2 Nf6 20. f3 Qh5 21. a4 Rae8 22. a5 e5 $1 23. dxe5 dxe5 24.
axb6 axb6 25. Ra7 Re7 26. b5 Rfe8 27. Kg1 {Black's most important resource is
to play ...f4, and this was already possible!} Qf7 (27... f4 $1 28. gxf4 exf4
29. Bxf6 Qg6+ 30. Kh1 Qxf6 $15) 28. Qc2 f4 $1 $132 29. Rea1 $2 (29. gxf4 {
was necessary.} e4 $5 (29... exf4 30. Qf5 $1 $11)) 29... e4 $1 $19 {Now
Black's attack is too strong.} 30. Ra8 fxg3 31. hxg3 Nh5 32. Rxe8+ Rxe8 33.
fxe4 Qg6 34. Qd3 Nxg3 35. Kh2 Rxe4 36. Rg1 Rh4+ 37. Kg2 Ne4+ 0-1

