1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. d4 Bb4+ 4. Nc3 d5 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 c5 7. O-O Nc6 8. a3
Bxc3 9. bxc3 Qc7 10. cxd5 exd5 {It seems that we already examined this
structure, but here is an important difference - White's knight is on f3
instead of e2! This detail is in Black's favour since the plan with f3-e4 is
no longer available.} 11. h3 Re8 12. Bb2 (12. dxc5 Na5 $132) 12... c4 13. Bc2 (
{After} 13. Be2 {Black would take full control of the important e4-square.} Bf5
) 13... Ne4 14. Nd2 (14. Bxe4 $2 Rxe4 $1 (14... dxe4 $5 $15) 15. Nd2 Re8 16. e4
dxe4 17. Nxc4 Ne7 18. Ne5 Be6 $15 {[%csl Gc4,Gd5] Black gets a strong blockade
on the light squares.}) 14... Bf5 15. Nxe4 Bxe4 16. Bxe4 Rxe4 $15 {Black is
better - it is not possible for White to push f3-e4.} 17. Bc1 Re6 18. Qh5 Qd7
19. Rb1 Na5 20. Re1 Rae8 21. Qf5 Nb3 22. Bb2 g6 23. Qf4 Re4 $19 {Now White is
already strategically lost - he can only sit passively while Black improves
his position.} 24. Qg3 f5 25. f4 Qe7 26. Kf2 Qg7 27. Rbd1 Qh6 28. Re2 a5 29. a4
Qg7 30. Qg5 h6 0-1

