1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. Nf3 d5 6. cxd5 exd5 7. Bf4 c5 8. e3
c4 {We get the same structure with a bishop on f4. White would rather have
this bishop on g5 to improve his control of e4.} 9. Be2 Nc6 10. O-O Ne7 11. Ne5
Bf5 12. Qc1 h6 {Black makes sure that the light-squared bishop can stay on the
b1-h7 diagonal.} 13. Bg3 (13. g4 Bh7) 13... Bxc3 14. bxc3 Ne4 15. Qb2 Qb6 16.
Qa3 Qe6 17. Rfc1 Nc8 18. Nf3 Nxg3 19. hxg3 Nd6 $17 {Black has taken full
control of the board. At some point, he may even exploit the "hook" on g3 to
start an attack with ...h5-h4.} 20. Nd2 Rfd8 21. Bf3 Bd3 22. Qc5 Ne4 23. Bxe4
dxe4 24. a4 Rd5 25. Qb4 Qc6 26. f3 f5 27. f4 Rb8 28. Ra2 b6 29. Rca1 Rc8 30. a5
b5 31. a6 Kf7 32. Rb2 Rb8 33. Kf2 Rb6 34. Qa3 Rd6 35. Qc5 Qxc5 36. dxc5 Rxa6
37. Rxa6 Rxa6 38. Rxb5 Ke6 39. c6 Kd6 40. c7 Kxc7 41. Rxf5 Ra2 42. Ke1 Ra1+ 43.
Kf2 Rd1 44. Rf7+ Kd6 45. Rxa7 Rxd2+ 46. Kg1 Re2 0-1

