1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. d4 b6 5. e3 O-O 6. Bd3 d5 7. O-O c5 8. cxd5
exd5 9. a3 Bxc3 10. bxc3 c4 11. Bc2 Bg4 12. Qe1 $1 {The same motif as in the
previous game in a slighty different position.} Nc6 $2 {Compared to the
previous game, Black has played the useless ...b6 instead of ...Qc7 and Wang
uses this to his advantage.} ({Black should have preferred} 12... Bxf3 13. gxf3
Qd7 14. Kh1 Qh3 15. Qe2 Nc6 16. Rg1 Nh5 {White may be better, but Black has
some counterchances.}) 13. Ne5 $3 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Nd7 15. f4 f5 16. a4 $18 {
White has a huge positional advantage which he managed to convert.} Nc5 17. Ba3
Rf7 18. Qd2 Ne4 19. Qd4 Qd7 20. a5 b5 21. a6 Qc6 22. Rfb1 h6 23. Bxe4 dxe4 24.
