1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 h6 $6 7. Nf3 d5 8.
e3 {White prefers to put his dark-squared bishop on b2 rather than on the more
exposed f4-square.} Nbd7 9. b4 ({It would be a positional mistake to play} 9.
cxd5 exd5 {since this opens the diagonal of the c8-bishop and also the e-file
for Black's rook.}) 9... c6 10. Bb2 Ne4 11. Qc2 a5 12. Bd3 f5 $2 $16 {Black's
follows the wrong strategy.} 13. O-O Qe7 14. b5 g5 15. cxd5 cxd5 16. a4 $18 {
Black has no attack on the kingside, while White is threatening to enter on
the c-file.} Qg7 17. Kh1 Rf7 18. Nd2 Ndf6 19. f3 Rc7 20. Qd1 Nxd2 21. Qxd2 b6
22. Ba3 Qd7 23. Rac1 Raa7 24. Qf2 Rxc1 25. Rxc1 Rc7 26. Rc2 Bb7 27. Qd2 Qc8 28.
Bd6 Rxc2 29. Qxc2 Qxc2 30. Bxc2 Nd7 31. Kg1 Kf7 32. Kf2 Kf6 33. Bc7 $18 {
This minor piece ending is winning for White. Black can never get rid of the
c7-bishop. White managed to open the kingside and he converted his advantage.}
Kf7 34. h3 Kf6 35. Bd8+ Kf7 36. f4 Kg6 37. g4 Ba8 38. Kg3 Bb7 39. Bd3 Ba8 40.
gxf5+ exf5 41. fxg5 hxg5 42. h4 gxh4+ 43. Kf4 Nf6 44. Bxf5+ Kf7 45. Bxb6 Ne4
46. Bxa5 Nd6 47. Be1 Nxf5 48. Kxf5 h3 49. Bg3 Ke7 50. a5 1-0

