1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nf3 c5 7. O-O dxc4 8. Bxc4
cxd4 9. exd4 Nbd7 (9... b6 {is the most common move.}) 10. Bg5 Bxc3 $1 {
This is a very good idea in my opinion. Black should take on c3 now, before
White has played Rc1.} 11. bxc3 Qc7 {After the c-file is closed, the queen is
well-placed on c7.} 12. Qe2 b6 13. Ne5 {This is not the best move.} Nxe5 (13...
Nd5 $5) 14. dxe5 Nd7 15. Be7 Nxe5 $1 16. Bxf8 Nxc4 17. Be7 Bb7 $44 {Black has
good compensation for the exchange. In practice, Black even has the easier
game.} 18. Rfd1 Bd5 19. Bh4 Qc6 20. Rd4 Nd6 21. c4 Nf5 22. cxd5 Nxd4 23. Qg4
Qxd5 24. Rd1 e5 25. Bf6 Nf3+ 26. gxf3 Qxd1+ 27. Kg2 g6 28. Qe4 Re8 29. Qc6 Rf8
30. Bxe5 Qd8 31. Bf6 Qc8 32. Qa4 Qf5 33. Be7 Ra8 34. Qc6 Rc8 35. Qb7 g5 36. Bf6
g4 37. f4 Re8 38. Be5 f6 0-1

