1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Qc2 d6 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 Nbd7 7. f3 a5 {
This is comparatively slow. Black should instead strike in the centre. Since
White has superiority in the centre, he can ignore the idea of ...a4.} 8. e4 e5
9. Ne2 a4 10. Be3 O-O 11. O-O-O $16 {I like this idea. Black can secure some
strong squares for his pieces by taking on d4, but he does not have any pawn
play! White, on the other hand, can attack with his pawns on the kingside.} b6
12. g4 Ra5 13. h4 Re8 14. h5 h6 15. Kb1 Nh7 16. Ng3 exd4 17. Bxd4 f6 18. Be2
Bb7 19. Rhe1 Ng5 20. Rd2 Nc5 {Black has found secure outposts for his knights,
but this is only enough to reduce White's advantage. Black cannot create
active counterplay, and White managed to win.} 21. Bd1 Nce6 22. Bg1 Qa8 23. Nf5
Bc6 24. Ka1 Re5 25. Be3 Nc5 26. Bd4 Nce6 27. Bxe5 fxe5 28. Bc2 Kh8 29. Red1 Nf4
30. Re1 Nge6 31. Rg1 Ng5 32. Re1 Bd7 33. Re3 Nge6 34. Rd1 Qd8 35. Ree1 Qg5 36.
Ne3 Ra8 37. Nd5 Qd8 38. Nxf4 Nxf4 39. Rd2 Ra5 40. Rg1 Qg5 41. Qb4 Ne6 42. Rgd1
Be8 43. Kb1 Nd4 44. Rxd4 exd4 45. Rxd4 Qe3 46. Rd3 Qg1+ 47. Rd1 Qf2 48. Qc3 Bf7
49. Bd3 Rc5 50. Qc2 Qg3 51. Qe2 Qf4 52. Rc1 Bg8 53. Rc3 Qg3 54. Qe3 Be6 55. Be2
Bg8 56. Qd4 Qe1+ 57. Qd1 Qf2 58. Qd3 Qg1+ 59. Rc1 Qg3 60. Qe3 Bf7 61. Rg1 Qh2
62. Rc1 Qg3 63. Bd3 Be6 64. Rg1 Qh2 65. Rc1 Qg3 66. Rg1 Qh2 67. Rc1 Qg3 68. Qe2
Qf4 69. Rc3 Bg8 70. Bc2 Ra5 71. Qe3 Qg3 72. Qd4 Qf4 73. Qd1 Rc5 74. Bxa4 Bxc4
75. Bb3 Bxb3 76. Qxb3 Qe5 77. Rxc5 Qxc5 78. Qc3 Qg1+ 79. Qc1 Qg2 80. Qxc7 Qf1+
81. Ka2 Kh7 82. Qxb6 Qc4+ 83. Qb3 Qc5 84. a4 1-0

