1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 d5 6. Nf3 c5 7. O-O Nc6 8. a3
Bxc3 9. bxc3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Qc7 11. Be2 e5 12. d5 Rd8 $2 {Black was counting on
this move, however, there is a refutation.} 13. e4 $1 {This positionally
desireable move is possible due to tactics.} Na5 (13... Nxe4 {loses material.}
14. Qc2 Bf5 15. Bd3 $18) 14. Bg5 $16 {White has a serious positional advantage.
} Qd6 (14... Nxe4 15. Bxd8 Qxd8 16. Qc2 Nd6 17. Nxe5 $18) 15. Nd2 h6 16. Be3 (
16. Bh4 {is also better for White but it might offer some hope for Black.} g5
17. Bg3 Bd7 18. h4 Kg7) 16... Nd7 17. f4 $1 $18 f6 18. c4 {White could also
have played f5, but he is not afraid of ...exf4.} b6 (18... exf4 19. Bxf4 Ne5
20. Nf3 Nxf3+ 21. Rxf3 Qe7 22. Qc2 $18 (22. Rg3 $18) (22. Re3 $6 {needlessly
allows} Nc6)) 19. f5 {White slowly but surely will win by advancing his pawns
on the kingside.} Nf8 20. Rf3 (20. g4 $5) 20... Qe7 21. Rg3 Kh8 22. h4 Nb7 23.
Rh3 Nd6 24. g4 Nh7 25. a4 $1 Bd7 26. Bd3 $1 Be8 27. Nf3 Nf7 28. Ra2 $1 {
The rook joins the attack via the 2nd rank.} Kg8 29. Rg2 Rd6 30. Kf2 Rc8 31.
Qh1 Bxa4 32. g5 fxg5 33. hxg5 Nhxg5 34. Bxg5 hxg5 35. Nxg5 Nxg5 36. Rh8+ Kf7
37. Qh5+ g6 38. fxg6+ Rxg6 39. Rh7+ 1-0

