{The player with the black pieces played a great game up to some point, though
ultimately,White won.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 O-O 5. Bd3 c5 6. Nf3
b6 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3 Bb7 9. Qe2 Ne4 10. Bb2 f5 11. Nd2 Nxd2 12. Qxd2 d6 13.
f3 Nd7 14. e4 $2 {White committs a serious positional mistake.} f4 $1 15. Rad1
e5 $1 16. Bc2 Bc6 $1 $17 {Black calmly defends against White's threats on the
d-file, leaving him with to powerless bishops.} 17. dxc5 dxc5 18. Qe2 (18. Qd6
Rf6) 18... Qc7 19. Rd5 Nf6 20. Rfd1 Rad8 21. R1d2 Bxd5 22. cxd5 Ne8 (22... c4
$1 $19) 23. c4 Nd6 $4 (23... Qe7 24. Ba4 Nd6 25. Bc6 Qf6 $19) 24. Bxe5 $18 {
After blundering the e5-pawn, Black is suddenly lost.} Qe7 25. Bxd6 Rxd6 26. e5
Rh6 27. d6 Qh4 28. h3 Qg5 29. e6 Rxh3 30. e7 1-0

